Process_Handling_Commands
-------------------------
To suspend a job, type CLTR+Z while it is running. you can also suspend a job with CLTR+Y

CLTR+Z : in that the process is only stopped when it attempts to read input from terminal.

CLTR+C , to interrupt a job.

1) myCommand & : #runs job in the background and prompts back to shell

2)jobs  : #lists all jobs (use with -l to see associated PID).

3)fg  : # brings background into foreground.

4) kill -l : #returns a list of all signals on the system

5)kill PID : # terminates process with specific PID

6)ps : prints a line of information about the current running 

7)wait  :# waits untill all background jobs have finished.

